'''菲比·阿珀森·赫斯特'''（{{lang-en|Phoebe Apperson Hearst}}，{{bd|1842年|12月3日|1919年|4月13日}}），[[美國|美國]]慈善家、[[女權主義|女權主義]]者<ref>{{Cite journal| author = Nickliss, Alexandra | title = ''Phoebe Apperson Hearst's 'Gospel of Wealth,' 1883-1901'' | journal = Pacific Historical Review | volume = 71 |language=en | pages = 525-605|date=November 2002}}</ref>。她同時也是報業大王[[威廉·赫斯特|威廉·赫斯特]]的母親。

==生平==
菲比·赫斯特出生於[[密蘇里州|密蘇里州]]{{link-en|聖克萊爾|Saint Clair, Missouri}}。19歲時嫁給後來成為美國[[參議員|參議員]]的[[喬治·赫斯特|喬治·赫斯特]]。婚後不久這對年輕夫婦便搬到[[加州|加州]][[舊金山|舊金山市]]，在那裡菲比生下兩人唯一的獨子：[[威廉·赫斯特|威廉]]。

在1880年代，她是位積極的慈善家。她是金門幼稚園協會的主要贊助者與董事<ref>{{Cite book | author = Edward T. James, ed. | title = ''Notable American Women 1607-1950'' | publisher = Belknap Press of Harvard University Press | year = 1971 | volume= II |language=en | page = 171 }}</ref>，同時也是加州世紀俱樂部的第一任主席<ref>{{en}}{{Cite book| author = Century Club of California | title = ''Historical Sketch'' | publisher = Century Club of California |language=en | year = 1893 }}</ref>。除此之外她還是美國[[柏克萊加州大學|加州大學柏克萊分校]]的第一位女性校董與贊助者。她自1897年起在董事會任職，直到去世。同樣在1897年，她促使全國母親代表大會的成立，該會為後來[[全國家長與教師協會|全國家長與教師協會]]的前身。1900年，她與其他人共同創立{{Link-en|國家大教堂學校|National Cathedral School}}，使得一座毗鄰該校的公立小學以她的名字命名以作紀念<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hearstdc.org/contact.htm|title=Welcome to Phoebe Hearst Elementary School!|publisher=Phoebe Hearst Elementary School|location=[[華盛頓特區|華盛頓特區]]|5=|language=en|accessdate=2011-05-23|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004231313/http://www.hearstdc.org/contact.htm|archivedate=2011-10-04}}</ref>。

1898年，她的[[宗教|宗教]]信仰從[[坎伯蘭長老教會|坎伯蘭長老教會]]<ref>{{en}}{{Cite book | author=Owens, Billie Louise and Robert James, | title = ''Sons of Frontiersmen:  History & Genealogy of Rowland, Whitmire and Associated Families'' | publisher = Billie Louise and Robert James Owens |language=en | year = 1976 | page = 62}}</ref>轉向[[巴哈伊教|巴哈伊教]]，並對該教在美國的傳播起了重要的影響。她在1898年12月14日抵達[[巴勒斯坦|巴勒斯坦]]（現[[以色列|以色列]]）境內的[[阿卡_(以色列)|阿卡]]與[[海法|海法]]兩地朝聖<ref>{{Cite book| title = ''Encyclopedia of Women and Religion in North America | url = https://archive.org/details/encyclopediawome00kell | first = Rosemary Skinner'' | last = Keller | first2 = Rosemary Radford | last2 = Ruether | first3 = Marie | last3 = Cantlon | publisher = Indiana University Press | year = 2006 |language=en | isbn =  0253346851 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/encyclopediawome00kell/page/n825 777]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book| title = ''Materials for the Study of the Bab́i ́religion'' | url = https://archive.org/details/materialsforstud0000brow | first = Edward Granville | last = Browne | publisher = The University Press |language=en | year = 1918 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/materialsforstud0000brow/page/n97 97]–98}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book| title = ''The Hearsts'' | url = https://archive.org/details/hearstsamericand0000robi | first = Judith | last = Robinson | publisher = University of Delaware Press | year = 1991 |language=en | isbn = 0874133831 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/hearstsamericand0000robi/page/311 311]–312}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book| last = Hatcher |last2 =  Martin | first2 = J.D. |year = 1998 |title = ''The Bahá'í Faith: The Emerging Global Religion'' | url = https://archive.org/details/bahaifaithemergi0000hatc |publisher = Harper & Row |location = San Francisco | pages = [https://archive.org/details/bahaifaithemergi0000hatc/page/52 52]–53 |language=en | isbn = 0877432643 <!--| unused_data = first W.S.-->}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book| title = ''Introduction to New and Alternative Religions in America'' | url = https://archive.org/details/introductiontone00gall | first = Eugene V. | last = Gallagher | first2 = W. Michael | last2 = Ashcraft | publisher = Greenwood Publishing Group | year = 2006 | isbn = 0275987124 |language=en | pages = [https://archive.org/details/introductiontone00gall/page/n208 192]–193}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book| title = ''The Origins of the Bahá'í Community of Canada, 1898-1948'' | url = https://archive.org/details/originsbahaicomm00hoon | first = Will C. | last = Van den Hoonaard | publisher = Wilfrid Laurier University Press | year = 1996 |language=en | isbn = 0889202729 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/originsbahaicomm00hoon/page/17 17], 36, 356 pages}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | title = ''Lights of the Spirit: Historical Portraits of Black Baha'is in North America, 1898-2000'' | first = Gwendolyn | last = Etter-Lewis | first2 = Richard Walter | last2 = Thomas | publisher = Baha'i Publishing Trust |language=en | year = 2006 | isbn = 1931847266 | pages = 23, 176}}</ref>，她後來描述道：「這三天是我生命中最難忘的日子。」（Those three days were the most memorable days of my life.）<ref>{{Cite book| title = ''Persia by a Persian: Personal Experiences, Manners, Customs, Habits, Religious and Social Life in Persia'' | first = Isaac | last = Adams | publisher = E. Stock | year= 1906 | location = [[紐約公共圖書館|紐約公共圖書館]] |language=en | pages = 489}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | author=Effendi, Shoghi | title=''God Passes By'' | location=Wilmette | publisher=Bahá'í Pub. Trust | year=1974 |language=en | isbn=0-87743-020-9}}</ref>

她在1919年4月13日死於[[西班牙流感|西班牙流感]]，享年76歲。逝世後被安葬在[[加州|加州]][[聖馬刁縣|聖馬刁郡]][[科爾馬市|科爾馬市]]內的{{Link-en|賽普拉斯草坪紀念公園|Cypress Lawn Memorial Park}}<ref>{{Cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|coauthors=|title=Phoebe Apperson Hearst (1842-1919)|url=http://www.hearstcastle.org/history/phoebe_hearst.asp|work=|publisher=Hearst Castle|language=en|date=|accessdate=2007-06-18|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070629092413/http://www.hearstcastle.org/history/phoebe_hearst.asp|archivedate=2007-06-29}}</ref>
